The Freeport of Riga has implemented all recommendations of the State Council regarding the Krievu Island project.
The Freeport of Riga Authority has implemented all of the five recommendations of the State Audit Office regarding the implementation of the project Infrastructure Development in Krievu Island for the transfer of port activities from the city center, Diena.lv portal was informed by the company.
The approval of the project is planned at the next board meeting of the Freeport of Riga.
In order for the recommendations to be implemented according to the opinion of the SC, by preparing the necessary documentation for the implementation of the recommendations, the Riga Freeport Authority was also guided by the conclusions of the legal and operational audit conducted by the international auditor Deloitte at the Riga Freeport Authority and the recommendations provided for improving the project management in the future project stage.
Information on the implementation of the recommendations has also been sent to VK today.
Despite the fact that the Riga Freeport Authority does not agree with the opinion prepared by the Supreme Court on the usefulness of the implementation of the Krieviu Island project, we treat the implementation of the project and the funding provider - the European Commission (EC) very responsibly.
I would like to emphasize that all the construction works planned as part of the project have been fully completed within the set deadlines and in the planned scope.
&quot;In order to prove to all those involved in the implementation of the project, including EC, VC and stevedores, that the main goal of the Freeport is to successfully implement the project, we have fully implemented all VC&#39;s recommendations regarding project management and monitoring issues,&quot; says Sanita Kaire, Krievu Island project manager.
In order to control and monitor the achievement of the project goal, the existing long-term action plan was supplemented with the most important planned activities of the involved parties and the deadlines for the necessary decisions, the definitions of meetings and regular reports and their deadlines, the monitoring tools of the planned construction process, as well as the definitions of the most important border points.
The approved action plan for achieving the project&#39;s goal by December 31, 2018, in accordance with the recommendations of the SC, was supplemented with execution monitoring activities, thus strengthening the control of the deadlines for the activities of other parties involved in the implementation of the project on the part of the Freeport of Riga.
In order to improve project management and reduce potential risks, a new project management plan has been developed, defining the areas of project management and specifying the developed documents that provide a control and monitoring mechanism for each of them.
In order to increase the capacity of the project, a project management structure diagram has been developed, which reflects the planned structure of the project management team, the qualifications and functions of the employees.
In order to improve the communication of the Freeport of Riga Authority with the parties involved in the project, a communication plan of the parties interested in the project has been developed, which, in addition to the parties specified in the project action plan, defines the parties interested in the successful completion of the project, the principles, types and periodicity of information exchange.
On the other hand, in order to improve the control of the use of financial resources, the necessity of concluding a service contract or starting a procurement will have to be substantiated in more detail in the future, as well as legality.
As part of the project, a port infrastructure that meets world standards has been built on Krievu Island - four new deep-water berths, railway feeders, as well as engineering communications.
The buildings co-financed by the Cohesion Fund have been completed and put into operation already at the end of last year, achieving a saving of 10.6 million euros in the funding provided for it.
