The reconstruction of the VEF Palace of Culture will finally start this week.
The palace will be renovated by SIA &quot;Velve&quot; for approximately 11 million euros.
It is planned to renovate several palace rooms, including two auditoriums, as well as adapt the building for people with mobility impairments.
The Riga City Council intends to attract European Union funds for the project in the amount of six million euros, however, Director of the Property Department of the Riga City Council, Oļegs Burovs, admits that there is still no complete clarity about European funds for the project.
&quot;Despite the fact that there is a political will to start repairs to the VEF Culture Palace by attracting European structural funds, we are waiting for months for a decision, a real action from the officials of the Ministry of Finance, whether the money will be allocated or not&quot;, says Burov.
Last December we were told that everything depends on Brussels.
Two weeks ago, the Ministry of Finance received a letter from the European Commission that you should make your own decision, that Brussels does not make a decision here.
At the moment we see that another round of discussion is forming, well, then we will see what we can expect in the coming days.
