The second - improvement of the service offer of VEF Culture Palace.
It is planned to restore the building&#39;s interior, walls and ceilings, improve the stage and sound recording studio, as well as arrange the building&#39;s internal engineering communications.
Third - Improvement of working conditions of creative amateur collectives, which includes plans to improve workshop equipment, room heating and ventilation systems.
Before the 40th anniversary of &quot;Livu&quot;, you can get to know the legendary rock band at an exhibition in Liepāja.
The exhibition will feature various items characterizing &quot;Livus&quot; - photos arranged in a timeline to reflect the group&#39;s activities from the beginning until 2010, when the end of the group&#39;s activities was announced.
The participants&#39; stage costumes, musical instruments, awards and concert recordings will also be shown, as well as other things that have not yet been seen by the general public, which reflected the creative activity of the &quot;Līvi&quot; group.
The exhibition will be supplemented with items from the collection of the Liepāja Museum.
The visual design of the exhibition was created in collaboration with fashion artist and painter Elita Patmalnieci.
The musicians who were associated with the group &quot;Līvi&quot; and their relatives responded to the invitation and shared both objects and memories.
The beginnings of &quot;Livu&quot; can be traced back to 1972, when a vocal-instrumental ensemble was created in the Liepāja House of Culture, led by Juris Pavītols.
In its original composition, the ensemble participated in the festival &quot;Liepājas dzintars&quot; in 1972 and 1974, as well as in city and republic shows.
The fateful meeting took place in 1976, when Juris Pavītols met Ārik Ķiģeli and founded a group at the Metalurga Palace of Culture, inviting Ingrīda Gūtmani, Andri Krūziņa and Jānis Groduma to join.
Over the years, the composition of the group has changed more than once.
Members have joined, others have gone their separate ways, some have returned.
However, the most important thing - the desire to prove that Latvian rock music is capable of living and existing - has remained unchanged.
&quot;There was no shortage of things to see - in jeans, hairy and bearded, these boys noticeably differed from the generally accepted stereotype of pop singers,&quot; says music reviewer Klaas Vävere about the group.
In addition to the aforementioned musicians, such excellent musicians as Igo, Vilnis Krieviņš, Modris Šterns, Valdis Štarks, Laimis Rācenājs, Tālis Pusbarnieks, Ainars Virga, Aivars Brīze, Guntars Mucenieks, Dainis Virga, Tomas Klein and many others have worked in the group.
Entrance to the exhibition is free.
The exhibition can be viewed from August 19 to October 30.
On the other hand, on August 27, the &quot;LĪVIfest 2&quot; celebration of the 40th anniversary of the group &quot;Līvi&quot; will be held at the &quot;Pūt, vējiņi&quot; concert garden in Liepāja.
Inflation is observed in Bulgaria for the first time in 8 months.
In July, Bulgaria&#39;s national statistics showed 1% monthly inflation.
This is the highest indicator since 2012 and the first indicator above zero since October last year, when it was positive (0.2%).
Annual average inflation according to CPI, in the last 12 months (August 2015 - July 2016), compared to the previous year, was -0.8%.
The consumer price index in July 2016 compared to the previous year was 101.9% and the monthly average inflation was 1.0%.
Year-to-date inflation was -0.2% (July 2016 compared to December 2015) and annual inflation in July 2016 compared to July 2015 was -0.2%.
Compared to the previous month, in July 2016 there was an increase in prices for the following groups of consumer goods: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1.7%); transport (1.8%); entertainment and cultural events (6.3%); hotels and restaurants (1.2%); household goods and services (0.3%).
Prices decreased for clothing and footwear (2.2%); for housing equipment, household appliances and regular house cleaning (0.5%); for health (0.1%).
Prices remained at the previous month&#39;s level for alcohol and tobacco, management, water, electricity, gas and other types of fuel, communications and education.
