However, she later changed her mind - in her submission to Finance Minister Dana Reizniece-Ozola on Friday, she states that she is withdrawing her consent to the transfer to the position of head of the SRS and that this is not an easy choice for her.
Andrejs Vaivars, the press secretary of Prime Minister Māras Kučinskas, explained to the LETA agency that a new competition will be held for the vacant position of Director General of the SRS.
