The reconstructed section of the road has been opened in Medumi.
The Minister of Transport Uldis Augulis, the management of VAS Latvijas Valsts ceļi (LVC), as well as representatives of builders SIA &quot;Binders&quot; and representatives of local governments, today opened the reconstructed section of the main state highway Russian border (Grebņeva) - Rēzekne - Daugavpils - Lithuanian border (Medumi) (A13) from Medumi to the Lithuanian border (156.4-163.05 km).
Roads are the calling card of the country, especially the border roads, so it is a special satisfaction to discover a reconstructed section on the border with our southern neighbours.
This is another example of the fact that, thanks to the co-financing of European Union funds, the situation on the country&#39;s main highways is improving.
&quot;According to the forecasts, the funds available for roads during this planning period will be used up already in 2018, and we have to think about how to continue to maintain the busiest roads in very good quality, and also ensure the mobility of the population in all regions of Latvia without European Union funding&quot;, he emphasized while cutting the symbolic ribbon Uldis Augulis.
The Minister of Transport also indicated that proposals prepared by traffic experts on sustainable financing of Latvian roads will be presented to the government in the near future.
Construction works on the section from Medumi to the Lithuanian border (km 156.4-163.05) were started by SIA Binders last year and continued this year after a technological break.
The cost of the reconstruction is 13.5 million euros (including VAT), the project was co-financed by the European Regional Development Fund (ERDF).
&quot;In the reconstructed section of the road, the structure of the road has been completely restored and next year, repair work will begin on the next section from Medumi to Daugavpils itself, thus the entire road from the Lithuanian border to Daugavpils will be repaired&quot;, informed Jānis Lange, chairman of the board of LVC.
The country&#39;s main highways are the most congested, and by 2018 we plan to have all the country&#39;s main roads in good condition.
The next task will be to maintain them in good quality, providing timely periodic maintenance and replacing the asphalt top layer every 7-9 years.
&quot;This, of course, will require adequate funding, and all road users are looking forward to the proposals developed by the expert group for the arrangement of the road financing system,&quot; noted Lange.
As part of the project, road connections and lighting in the center of Medumu have been arranged.
Considerable earthworks have been carried out: four stages of large-scale desalination and extensive trenching and embankment works, the longitudinal profile of the road, which was very uneven until now, has been leveled.
Public transport stops have also been renovated and a turning area for public transport has been rebuilt.
Previously, the road had insufficient bearing capacity and the terrain of the area was not transparent due to hilly valleys, and the old road copied the terrain.
In the next construction season, it is planned to restore the road section from the Daugavpils city border to the now reconstructed section (km 144.80-156.40).
This year, LVC plans to perform various types of work on more than 1,100 kilometers of national roads.
Information about all the repair works planned this year in the national road network is available on the LVC website www.lvceli.lv.
&quot;To achieve the desired weight loss results, the correct choice of food product combinations is very important,&quot; admits Lithuanian nutritionist Laura Romeraite-Kuklieriene.
Moreover, it is easy to do during the summer period, when fresh fruits, berries and vegetables grow in our own gardens.
A judicious combination of nutritional products can help not only to reduce excess weight, but also to promote various body processes in a targeted manner.
Macaroni and vinegar are a winning combination because they provide long-lasting satiety and help fight fat.
Research published in the European Journal of Clinical Nutrition has shown that vinegar has a beneficial effect on blood glucose levels and helps us feel alert.
Cayenne pepper and a protein-rich food, such as poultry or a protein shake, not only make you feel full, but also reduce cravings for large meals at subsequent meals.
Such a combination of foods can increase the amount of calories burned even after a meal by up to 35%.
Research shows that cayenne pepper can help get rid of belly fat.
Eggs contain the metabolism-boosting nutrient choline, while paprika is a good source of vitamin C.
Adequate intake of these nutrients can reduce cortisol levels, which in turn reduces fat accumulation around the midsection.
Oatmeal with fresh berries is another delicious and fat-burning breakfast meal worth adding to your menu.
Oatmeal and berries contain fiber, which, according to Canadian scientists, controls ghrelin - the appetite-stimulating hormone - and thus the feeling of hunger.
In addition, berries contain polyphenols, which help in weight loss and also prevent the formation of fat.
Vegetables and protein can also work wonders for weight loss.
Such a combination can create a feeling of satiety.
Vegetables contain water and fiber, so they promote satiety.
At the same time, proteins slow down the digestion process and ensure a feeling of satiety for a longer time.
For lunch, you can eat chicken with a salad or make a protein shake from the ready mixture and enjoy it together with your favorite vegetables.
What product combinations to avoid.
Fruits contain sugars - monosaccharides or disaccharides - compounds of one or two molecules.
In contrast, the starch found in vegetables is a polysaccharide.
Fruits break down mechanically in the stomach, while they do not break down chemically until they reach the third or fourth stage of digestion, which takes place in the intestines.
Starch breaks down into three different stages that begin in the mouth.
Therefore, it is important not to eat sweet food immediately after a meal.
Eating sweet food right after a meal gets it &quot;trapped&quot; in the stomach with other food, where it is not chemically digested and begins to rot.
Do not eat bread, potatoes, peas, bananas, dates, or other carbohydrate-containing foods with lemons, limes, oranges, grapefruit, pineapples, or other acidic fruits.
The enzyme ptyalin, which is present in saliva, only works in an alkaline environment.
Fruit acids not only inhibit the digestion of carbohydrates, but also promote their fermentation.
Do not eat eggs and meat, nuts and meat, cheese and eggs, or cheese and nuts, meat and milk, eggs and milk, or nuts and milk and similar combinations of protein-rich foods at the same meal.
Different digestive juices are needed to process them, each with different strength, characteristics and time to reach the stomach.
Watermelon, honeydew melon, cantaloupe and other melons should always be eaten separately from other foods.
Melons are not digested if they are in the stomach with other foods.
Fat in combination with protein-rich products.
Fat makes a successful combination with starch, but the same cannot be said for fat and protein - fat inhibits protein digestion.
Protein can be combined with a very small amount of fat.
If a large amount of protein-containing products are consumed, avoid the use of fat altogether.
This also applies to freshness - it is not recommended to combine a large amount of nuts (contains protein) with a whole avocado (contains fat).
Such a combination hinders effective weight loss.
How to cook better?
&quot;Cooking food, heat treatment causes a significant loss of nutrients - approximately 15% to 55% of the original nutrient content of the products,&quot; says the nutritionist.
In most cases, nutrients are lost when food is boiled in water.
However, the nutritional value of some foods is enhanced by direct cooking.
After cooking the vegetables, it is recommended to use the remaining liquid to make soup - in this case, you will not lose the nutrients left in the water, and you can eat them later.
It is recommended to cook vegetables by steaming them as well.
Heat treatment significantly increases the bioavailability of lycopene in tomatoes.
Boiling tomatoes for 30 minutes increases the amount of lycopene by 25%.
Heat treatment also greatly increases the bioavailability of beta-carotene, which is found in red, yellow, orange vegetables such as tomatoes, carrots, sweet potatoes and spinach.
Heat treatment of eggs and meat takes away the natural properties of the proteins in them, making them easier to digest.
Similarly, heat treatment of meat and eggs makes the iron and other minerals contained in these products easier to be absorbed by the body.
It should also be kept in mind that freezing products can reduce the amount of vitamin C from 10% to up to 90%, but freezing does not affect fiber.
Beans in combination with tomatoes can increase the absorption of iron in the body, which in turn ensures better brain and muscle function.
Our body absorbs up to 33% less non-hematopoietic iron, found in plant products such as beans, leafy greens, cereal products, than hematopoietic iron found in animal products such as beef, fish and chicken.
You can greatly increase your body&#39;s absorption of non-hematopoietic iron by eating foods containing non-hematopoietic iron along with sources of vitamin C, such as oranges, tomatoes, and berries.
Vitamin C helps to change the non-blood-forming iron so that it is more easily absorbed by our body.
Iron is necessary for the production of hemoglobin, which ensures the delivery of oxygen to the muscles and brain.
To get the most out of your salad, add healthy fats like olive or flaxseed oil.
When making salmon sandwiches, add vitamin D-rich salmon or sardines to plain yogurt, which is a good source of calcium.
Vitamin D increases the amount of calcium absorbed in the intestines and plays an important role in bone formation.
Oats (as well as other whole grains) along with sources of vitamin C, such as strawberries, blackcurrants, raspberries and other fruits or berries, help stabilize cholesterol levels as well as prevent clogging of the arteries.
Snapchat&#39;s &quot;Anime&quot; effect is criticized for caricaturing Asians
Snapchat officials say the filter was inspired by the animation, but some commenters say it&#39;s racially insensitive.
With this lens effect, Snapchat allows its 150 million users to alter reality and play with their identity in an absurd way every day.
You can turn yourself into a pineapple, a dog or a character that would fit in a Roy Lichtenstein painting.
Lenses are nebulous, image-distorting tools that generate more than 30 million altered selfies a day.
Any mistake quickly becomes public.
Snapchat&#39;s lens effects have been criticized in the past, with accusations that the app promotes skin tones that are too dark or too light as the standard of ideal beauty.
The new lens effects, which allow users to create crooked eyes, crooked teeth and round cheeks, were released this week, with some critics calling it a racist caricature of Asians - the &quot;yellow face&quot;.
The question was also asked whether such contradictions do not indicate that the company has bigger problems with diversity.
The news and public backlash erupted on Wednesday when The Verge and Motherboard reported that lens effects had been removed from the app.
The company explained that the purpose of the lens is to represent Anime characters, not to caricature people of Asian descent.
But for people who have experienced racism, these effects resembled painful stereotypes.
Others categorically denied the resemblance to Anime.
Korean-American art student Grace Sparapani&#39;s Twitter post about the images went viral. In an email, she says the lens effects are &quot;offensive and embarrassing, to say the least.&quot;
She added that it&#39;s hard not to notice the obvious similarity between Asian caricatures and lens effects.
This suggests that the lens effect is not simply yellow face, but yellow face in the sense of racism.
Snapchat isn&#39;t the only company that has fallen into this cultural trap.
American culture is also engaged in a never-ending battle for diversity and inclusion, from corporate boardrooms to Hollywood to the devices we use every day.
And Snapchat&#39;s large, racially diverse youth audience, unlike its older population, is more sensitive to such things.
If Snapchat lenses create an image that offends users, &quot;things like this don&#39;t go unnoticed these days,&quot; 25-year-old Katie Zhou said in an interview on Thursday.
Zhou, product manager at Medium, deleted her Snapchat app on Thursday and advised others to do the same.
In her Medium article and in a phone interview, she explained that she believes issues related to race stem from Snapchat&#39;s employment policies that don&#39;t support racial diversity enough.
Zhou criticized the company&#39;s predominantly white male leadership and then ended his article with the hashtag #DeleteSnapchat.
&quot;It means that there is no racial diversity in the company, so these decisions are made. Are there some people of other races working in the company, but they are not in a position where they can safely and comfortably express their opinion,&quot; says Chinese-American Zhou.
Others agree with her, while Snapchat has not responded to her complaint.
The company does not disclose how many employees are racially diverse, saying it is a privately held company.
Snapchat declined to discuss the backgrounds of its employees, but a spokesperson revealed that the company has hired an HR specialist who will focus on bringing underrepresented racial minorities to the company and promoting inclusion.
Zhou, on the other hand, will not update his Snapchat account, adding: &quot;I wonder if they really need more users like us to realize that this is wrong.&quot;
