The future of a Portland smelter is becoming uncertain as a major contract is terminated.
The future of an aluminum smelter and hundreds of its workers in Portland, Victoria has become uncertain after its main customer, an energy company, announced the termination of cooperation.
The announcement follows plans by the Victorian Government to end subsidies to the energy company, which are vital to the company&#39;s continued operation.
The 20-year subsidies will end in November.
