&quot;Latvenergo&quot; follows the gas market opening process also from the position of a potential trader.
The state energy company &quot;Latvenergo&quot; follows the process of opening the gas market from the position of both a consumer and a potential trader, said the company&#39;s press secretary Ivita Bidere.
&quot;The decision on whether Latvenergo will join the gas market as a trader in the future will be determined by what gas market model and legal regulation will be created.&quot;
&quot;That is why we are actively involved in the creation and commenting of regulatory acts, as well as submitting our proposals&quot;, said Bidere.
Agency BNS already wrote that the Ministry of Economy (ME) in cooperation with the Public Services Regulatory Commission and energy company &quot;Latvijas Gāze&quot; has developed the Cabinet of Ministers&#39; draft &quot;Regulations on the sale and use of natural gas&quot; which will change the existing operating principles of the natural gas market, from April 3, 2017 providing natural gas users with the right to freely choose a natural gas trader.
Working on the new regulation of the natural gas market, the goal of EM is to make the natural gas trading process as simple as possible and understandable to the user.
Therefore, the &quot;dealer-centric model&quot; was chosen as the most efficient and user-friendly service solution, in which all actions related to customer service are provided by the dealer - one contract, one invoice and one place for providing information and customer service, leaving the technical issues of the natural gas distribution system to the discretion of the distribution system operator.
A similar solution is currently implemented in electricity trading.
We remind you that a gradual opening of the market is planned for household users - even after April 3, 2017, those household users who do not want to choose another natural gas trader will be able to continue receiving natural gas from the existing trader at a regulated price, thus becoming connected users.
&quot;In this case, the obligation to supply natural gas to related users at a regulated price is determined by the public trader&quot;, informed the ministry.
On the other hand, merchants will have to choose a natural gas trader, with whom a natural gas sales contract must be concluded.
Until the conclusion of the natural gas trade agreement, natural gas trade will be provided by the current natural gas trader at the price determined by the natural gas trader for a certain period of time.
The draft regulations of the Cabinet of Ministers stipulate in detail the rights and obligations of natural gas traders, system operators and users.
The rules determine the procedure for supplying natural gas to users and interrupting its supply, the requirements for the safe use of the natural gas system, the rights and obligations of the trader, public trader, system operator, user and the owner of the gasified object in the supply and use of natural gas; the procedure for making payments for the services received, the amount of late payment interest, the procedure for changing traders and the supply of users in the event of natural gas supply disruptions; procedure by which natural gas supply to related users is provided by the public trader.
