The turnover of canned food producer &quot;Zilā lagūna&quot; decreased by 33.8% last year.
The turnover of canned food producer &quot;Zilā lagūna&quot; last year was 4.202 million euros, which is 33.8% less than a year earlier, while the company&#39;s losses decreased 5.7 times - to 904.7 thousand euros, according to the annual financial statements published in the &quot;Lursoft&quot; database overview.
The report of the company&#39;s management states that in 2015 the company worked with losses due to several reasons, including the permanent lack of working capital caused by the departure of &quot;Unicredit Bank&quot; from the Baltic market, terminating the previously valid credit line, and leaving the &quot;Blue Lagoon&quot; &quot; with concluded contracts without the possibility of fulfilling them.
Consequently, the company did not have sufficient funds to purchase cheaper raw materials in large quantities and receive a volume discount.
The relevant bank&#39;s withdrawal from the Latvian market also prevented the company from implementing European Union structural fund support projects, which would have allowed the production plant to purchase new production equipment and modernize the infrastructure.
Also, last year, the company&#39;s financial creators were negatively affected by the increase in the prices of raw materials and the reluctance of customers to pay more for the goods produced by the company.
&quot;Only in the second half of July 2016, customers recognized the price changes and were ready to buy goods at the new - higher - prices&quot;, says the company&#39;s management.
Also, in 2015, &quot;Zilā lagūna&quot; started negotiations with potential investors, including the valuation of the company&#39;s movable and immovable property.
The investors have already been to the company&#39;s largest creditor, Unicredit Leasing, where the parties have met and discussed possible investment plans.
At the same time, the company&#39;s operation and development were positively affected by the implementation of the restructuring and optimization plan started in 2014 and 2015.
This plan included the improvement and optimization of technological processes, which allows to achieve higher production productivity and capacity.
&quot;Several equipment was purchased, which ensures a higher production speed&quot;, the company&#39;s management stated.
The management of &quot;Zilā lagūna&quot; notes that the purchased equipment in 2016 will allow the company&#39;s production plant to fulfill orders that were not possible until now.
The first batch of products to be produced on this equipment will be ready in August.
Since the letters of intent have already been signed for the sale of the product, everything produced will be sold according to the letters of intent.
The new product will increase the turnover by about 300 thousand euros per month&quot;, says the company&#39;s management.
Also, in August 2016, the company plans to sign a cooperation agreement on the supply of fish products to Iraq.
In 2016, &quot;Blue Lagoon&quot; sent the first experimental container to Israel, expanded the market to Cyprus and this September will sign a cooperation agreement with a new supermarket chain in the USA.
As a result of all the above-mentioned measures, the company plans to increase turnover.
In 2014, &quot;Blue Lagoon&quot; worked with a turnover of 6.347 million euros and a loss of 5.113 million euros.
&quot;Blue Lagoon&quot; was founded in 1997 and its share capital is 1.156 million euros.
The company is owned by two Latvian private individuals - Mihailas Kaidanovas (89.11%) and Igors Širšons (10.89%).
